The paper deals with object proposals in computer vision, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the evaluation of object proposals, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). The authors perform exhaustive evaluations and cross-dataset generalization experiments, which are common in machine learning and statistical analysis (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the bias capacity in object proposal algorithms, which is a topic in cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the authors introduce a diagnostic experiment to detect bias, which is a topic in information retrieval (cs.IR).
